iche Volkssprachen auf gleichem geographischem Raum. Der Sammelband nähert sich diesem bisher nicht systematisch erschlossenen Themenfeld aus interdisziplinärer Perspektive. Er behandelt methodologische Grundsatzfragen sowie sprachliche und literarische Zeugnisse vom 8. bis ins 16. Jahrhundert.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aMultilingualismzGermanyxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aMehrsprachigkeit. 4aMittelalter / Literatur. 4aMittelalter / Sprache. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aMiddle Ages/Language.  aMiddle Ages/Literature.  aMultilingualism.1 aBALDZUHN, MICHAEL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBOK, VACLAV, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaldzuhn, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDREWELOWSKY, ANDRÉ, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEhlen, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGRUBMÜLLER, KLAUS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHAAG, GUNTRAM, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHAUBRICHS, WOLFGANG, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunt, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMEINEKE, ECKHARD, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPUTZO, CHRISTINE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPutzo, Christine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aREDZICH, CAROLA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWIELAND, GERNOT RUDOLF, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 